cumulativeSIRPerTEAx96 ~ uint176 ~ Q80.96 Worst case analysis assuming all SIR is accumulated by a single LPer AND it never gets claimed. If SIR uses 12 decimals after the comma, 'uint80' is sufficient to store ALL SIR issued over 599 years 2,015,000,000 sir/year * 599 years * 10^12 \u2264 type(uint80).max Maximum TEA Supply The previous choice implies that if wish to store struct LPerIssuanceParams in a single slot (256 bits), cumulativeSIRPerTEAx96 can use up to 96 bits for the decimals (Q80.96) It is important that cumulativeSIRPerTEAx96 does not underflow (if it is 0 it would wrongly imply that the LPers have not claim to any SIR): cumulativeSIRPerTEAx96 = 8/10 * 63.9 SIR/s * 10^12 * timeInterval * 2^96 * (tax / cumulativeTax) / T In the worst case scenario: timeInterval=1s, tax=1, cumulativeTax=type(uint16).max and TEA has 18 decimals. So to avoid underflow: T \u2264 8/10 * 63.9 * 10^12 * 2^96 / (2^16-1) If TEA has 18 decimals Max Supply of TEA = T / 10^18 \u2248 6.18 * 10^19 which is more than a Quintillion TEA, sufficient for almost any ERC-20."}},"kind":"user","methods":{"burn(bool,(address,address,int8),uint256)":{"notice":"Function for burning APE or TEA"},"initialize((address,address,int8))":{"notice":"Initialization is always necessary because we must deploy APE contracts, and possibly initialize the Oracle."},"mint(bool,(address,address,int8),uint256,uint144)":{"notice":"Function for minting APE or TEAThe user can also send ETH if the collateral token is WETH"},"totalReserves(address)":{"notice":"Global parameters for each type of collateral that aggregates amounts from all vaults (excluding fees to stakers) Fees to stakers can always be recovered by computing IERC20(collateral).balanceOf(address(this)) - totalReserves[collateral], so that if a token is accidentally sent to this contract, it becomes dividends for the stakers."},"withdrawToSaveSystem(address[],address)":{"notice":"This function is only intended to be called as last recourse to save the system from a critical bug or hackduring the beta period. getReserves((address,address,int8)).details: Kick it to periphery if more space is needed

updateSystemState(uint16,uint16,bool).details: All checks and balances to be done at system control

burn(bool,(address,address,int8),uint256.notice: Function for burning APE or TEA

initialize((address,address,int8)).notice: Initialization is always necessary because we must deploy APE contracts, and possibly initialize the Oracle.

mint(bool,(address,address,int8),uint256.notice: Function for minting APE or TEAThe user can also send ETH if the collateral token is WETH

totalReserves(address).notice: Global parameters for each type of collateral that aggregates amounts from all vaults (excluding fees to stakers) Fees to stakers can always be recovered by computing IERC20(collateral).balanceOf(address(this)) - totalReserves[collateral], so that if a token is accidentally sent to this contract, it becomes dividends for the stakers.

withdrawToSaveSystem(address[],address).notice: This function is only intended to be called as last recourse to save the system from a critical bug or hackduring the beta period. To execute it, the system must be in Shutdown statuswhich can only be activated after SHUTDOWN_WITHDRAWAL_DELAY seconds elapsed since Emergency status was activated.
